 [:db/add -5 :decision/summary "Algorithm always picks one seed and grows one contiguous zone per use type."]
 [:db/add -5 :decision/rationale "BFS guarantees contiguity, producing realistic zone coherence (real cities have a commercial core, not scattered shops). But entire budget concentrates in one area."]
 [:db/add -5 :decision/affects -1]

 [:db/add -6 :decision/summary "Reservation order determines which use type gets first pick of land."]
 [:db/add -6 :decision/rationale "First-reserved type gets the best location; later types work with whatever's left. This is the primary mechanism for expressing the archetype's organising principle."]
 [:db/add -6 :decision/affects -1]

 [:db/add -7 :decision/summary "Directional growth uses 2x score bonus along axis, 0.5x perpendicular, to produce elongated strips."]
 [:db/add -7 :decision/rationale "Commercial strips along roads, industrial strips along waterfronts need elongated rather than circular zones."]
 [:db/add -7 :decision/affects -1]

